Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer
exclusive Copyright and Related Rights (defined below) upon the creator
and subsequent owner(s) (each and all, an "owner") of an original work of
authorship and/or a database (each, a "Work").

Certain owners wish to permanently waive any and all Copyright and Related
Rights in a Work to the greatest extent allowed by law. For the avoidance
of doubt, those rights may include, but are not limited to, Copyright and
Related Rights in the Work and any works that are incorporated into or
are derivative works of the Work.

For the avoidance of doubt, the owner does not waive any exception or
limitation to Copyright and Related Rights that may apply to the owner
under applicable law. The owner makes the Waiver (defined below) and
public dedication (defined below) for the benefit of the public at large
and to the detriment of the owner's heirs and successors. The owner
fully understands and intends that the public dedication is irrevocable.

CC0 is a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, irrevocable dedication
to the public domain. For the full legal text, see:
https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode
